              "url": "/demo"
            },
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "text",
                "text": "demo page",
                "marks": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": " to get an overview what's UUI is capable to.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Why we built UUI?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "UUI started somewhere in 2013. We were building an app for EPAM, and we feel in love with the just born React and TypeScript so hard, that we were among the first production users of them. There were no UI libraries these days, so we built our own components set.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Components set from these days, were growing, traveling via tens of projects. We tried different approaches, picking the best fit. At some point, at 2016, we extracted them into a separate GIT repo. Later, we almost completely re-visit all the shortcomings and mistakes we've done. Twice. We changed the look-n-feel, three times.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "The current code base is a result of 7 years of evolution, each piece is 3-4 times rewritten from scratch. The team behind UUI built 3 comprehensive UI/UX Design Systems, and 10th of applications.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "At the start of 2020 we found ourselves as library used by almost 20 EPAM production projects. With all technical chooses settled, we praised backward-compatibility, and focused more on completeness of the solution, and helping existing projects. At the end of 2020, we are in the process to Open-Source UUI.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "note-link",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "UUI's value is not in lines of code, it's in 7 years of experience that lead to them.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Along the way, we looked into evolving marked of UI frameworks. Material UI, Ant.Design, and alike - where making great progress getting more stable and mature. But we were always a bit ahead in many aspects, and UUI match our needs better. ",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Which apps UUI fits?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "UUI is designed to build apps for our Employees. These apps are balancing between complexity of processes, and a strive to make UX better. In our apps, user interacts with app a lot. For us, user is not an observer, he's one who needs to get enough insight to make confident decisions. And to implement this decision without any ceremony.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "There are lots of apps which doesn't work this way. Instagram, Twitter, news sites - are intended to consume content, not for interaction.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "There's also an opposite end we never touch - a system of tables and forms. None of EPAM apps looks like that.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "So UUI is the best fit for apps, which evolves end-user interaction to explore and change. Think of Trello as a good example.  UUI fits great for issue trackers, HRMS, MDM, ERP, and CMS systems.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Probably, UUI is not the best fit for landing pages and news sites. However, we have such cases, and UUI works in these scenarios as well.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Explore our ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "object": "inline",
            "type": "link",
            "data": {
              "url": "demo"
            },
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "text",
                "text": "Demos",
                "marks": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": " to get an overview of the use-cases we support.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Is it a Framework or a library?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Some component libraries, build around the concept to not being a \"Framework\", but a \"Library\". React itself is an example. Being \"just a Library\" means not being opinionated, at all cost: do not dictate how you build your app, structure your code, do your state management. It's up to developer or architect to decide how to build particular app.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "In opposite, there is a \"Frameworks\" camp, like Angular. They see that it's really beneficial to have something that guides your team to success, with guidelines how to structure your code, how to manage state, and even in which folder to put each type of file. They often push this idea to the limits.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "UUI goes somewhere in between of two approaches. We don't completely drop an idea to help with some common application-wide tasks, like state-management, API calls, and error handing. But we doesn't force you to use any of this.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "note-link",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "We never dictate, we give a hand.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "We have tons of helpers which helps with:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "unordered-list",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "block",
            "type": "list-item",
            "data": {},
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "block",
                "type": "list-item-child",
                "data": {},
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "object": "text",
                    "text": "Form state management - including validation",
                    "marks": []
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "object": "block",
            "type": "list-item",
            "data": {},
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "block",
                "type": "list-item-child",
                "data": {},
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "object": "text",
                    "text": "List/Table/Tree state management - including lazy-loading, filtering, paging, etc.",
                    "marks": []
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "object": "block",
            "type": "list-item",
            "data": {},
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "block",
                "type": "list-item-child",
                "data": {},
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "object": "text",
                    "text": "Services - API calls with error-handing, convenient web-analytics events, managing modal windows",
                    "marks": []
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "object": "block",
            "type": "list-item",
            "data": {},
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "block",
                "type": "list-item-child",
                "data": {},
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "object": "text",
                    "text": "Stand-alone utilities to filter/sort data sets",
                    "marks": []
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "object": "block",
            "type": "list-item",
            "data": {},
            "nodes": [
              {
                "object": "block",
                "type": "list-item-child",
                "data": {},
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "object": "text",
                    "text": "Examples and guidelines how to combine this to build your UI",
                    "marks": []
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "However, if you want to have your own approach - UUI works just fine as a visual components library. The only thing we need, is to provide some context to it via our ContextProvider - as some components needs to know how, for example, use your Routing approach.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "But if you'll get into our helpers, you'll find that 80% of your screens can be build our of it like a breeze, without any complicated solution like Redux.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "uui-richTextEditor-header-3",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "More features to come",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "object": "block",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": {},
        "nodes": [
          {
            "object": "text",
            "text": "Our plan for 2021 is to:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
